.SH FUNCTIONS
.LP
.B
\fBgetBitmap(Id, [Option]) -> wxBitmap:wxBitmap()\fR
\fB                   when\fR
\fB                       Id :: unicode:chardata(),\fR
\fB                       Option ::\fR
\fB                           {client, unicode:chardata()} |\fR
\fB                           {size, {W :: integer(), H :: integer()}}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Query registered providers for bitmap with given ID.

.PP
Return: The bitmap if one of registered providers recognizes the ID or wxNullBitmap otherwise.


.RE
.B
\fBgetIcon(Id, [Option]) -> wxIcon:wxIcon()\fR
\fB                 when\fR
\fB                     Id :: unicode:chardata(),\fR
\fB                     Option ::\fR
\fB                         {client, unicode:chardata()} |\fR
\fB                         {size, {W :: integer(), H :: integer()}}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Same as \fIgetBitmap/2\fR, but return a \fIwxIcon\fR object (or ?wxNullIcon on failure).


.RE
